<br>
Her life had been turned upside down since Lanneth had disappeared from Surefall.  The premature birth of her daughter, the changes that had taken place in the Dragons, and now there was.......him.<br>
<br>
A small smile played on her lips as she thought of him.  They had hunted together many times in the past as members of allied guilds but somehow things had changed.  It had all started with the arguement they had had waiting to approach the great dragon, Vox.  He had dared to say that her late husband was less than a man because he was an elf.  She had been shocked at the audacity and arrogance of the human.  When he had spoken similiar words against Lanneth, she had become angry and spoken some harsh words in return.<br>
<br>
But he had continued to seek her out after that, calling her &quot;his rogue&quot;, arranging places for them to hunt.  The night he had informed of his intentions to marry her, she had been shocked.  If ever there were two completely different people, it was her and Craken.  He was a straight forward fighter with a thirst for the best in weapons and armor.  She was a sneaky and sometimes a dirty fighter, who would still be in Ravenscale if new armor hadn't practically fallen into her lap.<br>
<br>
She had figured to spend her life alone, with her daughter, after Lanneth's disappearance.  She still played the Thief, toying with the men who would seek her out.  But when Craken was around, her heart leapt to her throat and she found it difficult to play the game.<br>
<br>
The day he proposed, she finally admitted that the Thief had been caught by the fighter.  Her eyes had filled with tears as she accepted his offer of marriage.<br>
<br>
Marina giggled happily as her eyes once again focused on the beauty of the waterfall.  He had brought her here and shown her this wonderous site for the first time.  Standing, she brushed the clinging snow from her armor.  It was time to find him again.  Her warrior, her shield.  With a last happy smile at the water falling in a bright spray, she moved into the shadows and was gone.<br>
